{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/forests-in-mt-koya/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"1616500e-02eb-5aae-a29c-96fc23ae68e0","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b768785699fde5e3eeccd0480f3e369a/1f853/daimon.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.59375%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/b768785699fde5e3eeccd0480f3e369a/01472/daimon.webp 240w,\n/static/b768785699fde5e3eeccd0480f3e369a/222bd/daimon.webp 480w,\n/static/b768785699fde5e3eeccd0480f3e369a/620b9/daimon.webp 960w,\n/static/b768785699fde5e3eeccd0480f3e369a/86447/daimon.webp 1024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/b768785699fde5e3eeccd0480f3e369a/3bc27/daimon.jpg 240w,\n/static/b768785699fde5e3eeccd0480f3e369a/98431/daimon.jpg 480w,\n/static/b768785699fde5e3eeccd0480f3e369a/b3ee8/daimon.jpg 960w,\n/static/b768785699fde5e3eeccd0480f3e369a/1f853/daimon.jpg 1024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/b768785699fde5e3eeccd0480f3e369a/b3ee8/daimon.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Daimon of Mt.Koya\"\n          title=\"Daimon of Mt.Koya\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>  </p>\n<p>The first time I went to Mt.Koya. The purpose of this time was greeting Kukai-san and Dake-no-benzaiten-san.\nSpirits welcomed me at the entrance of the mountain.  </p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/9c2e505ea55b8a5ea57e274d0a5dc5f1/1f853/okunoin_1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.59375%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/9c2e505ea55b8a5ea57e274d0a5dc5f1/01472/okunoin_1.webp 240w,\n/static/9c2e505ea55b8a5ea57e274d0a5dc5f1/222bd/okunoin_1.webp 480w,\n/static/9c2e505ea55b8a5ea57e274d0a5dc5f1/620b9/okunoin_1.webp 960w,\n/static/9c2e505ea55b8a5ea57e274d0a5dc5f1/86447/okunoin_1.webp 1024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/9c2e505ea55b8a5ea57e274d0a5dc5f1/3bc27/okunoin_1.jpg 240w,\n/static/9c2e505ea55b8a5ea57e274d0a5dc5f1/98431/okunoin_1.jpg 480w,\n/static/9c2e505ea55b8a5ea57e274d0a5dc5f1/b3ee8/okunoin_1.jpg 960w,\n/static/9c2e505ea55b8a5ea57e274d0a5dc5f1/1f853/okunoin_1.jpg 1024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/9c2e505ea55b8a5ea57e274d0a5dc5f1/b3ee8/okunoin_1.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Okunoin\"\n          title=\"Okunoin\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>  </p>\n<p>First of all, I visited Okunoin. The place is so nice. It really expanded my sensibilities.  \nI dedicated my Shakyo(写経) there.  </p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7a8be43f30489224e77bd43cf6762fec/1f853/buddhistrosary.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.59375%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/7a8be43f30489224e77bd43cf6762fec/01472/buddhistrosary.webp 240w,\n/static/7a8be43f30489224e77bd43cf6762fec/222bd/buddhistrosary.webp 480w,\n/static/7a8be43f30489224e77bd43cf6762fec/620b9/buddhistrosary.webp 960w,\n/static/7a8be43f30489224e77bd43cf6762fec/86447/buddhistrosary.webp 1024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/7a8be43f30489224e77bd43cf6762fec/3bc27/buddhistrosary.jpg 240w,\n/static/7a8be43f30489224e77bd43cf6762fec/98431/buddhistrosary.jpg 480w,\n/static/7a8be43f30489224e77bd43cf6762fec/b3ee8/buddhistrosary.jpg 960w,\n/static/7a8be43f30489224e77bd43cf6762fec/1f853/buddhistrosary.jpg 1024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/7a8be43f30489224e77bd43cf6762fec/b3ee8/buddhistrosary.jpg\"\n          alt=\"a buddhist rosary\"\n          title=\"a buddhist rosary\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>  </p>\n<p>This is a buddhist rosary that is given as a memento of a donation for saving forests of Mt.Koya. I made a donation at the front desk in Okunoin.   \nEven though the mountain is crowded with many tour buses and cars, the air is so fresh.  \nThe overwhelming strength of forests grown by the local people seem hold the mountain district.  \nI empathize with local people’s will to live with the nature.  </p>\n<p>Mount Koya’s forests and their history<br>\n<a href=\"http://www.koyasan.or.jp/en/forest/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">http://www.koyasan.or.jp/en/forest/</a>  </p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d913c8359beea7a1d1cf9e862f92a8ec/1f853/okunoin_2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.59375%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/d913c8359beea7a1d1cf9e862f92a8ec/01472/okunoin_2.webp 240w,\n/static/d913c8359beea7a1d1cf9e862f92a8ec/222bd/okunoin_2.webp 480w,\n/static/d913c8359beea7a1d1cf9e862f92a8ec/620b9/okunoin_2.webp 960w,\n/static/d913c8359beea7a1d1cf9e862f92a8ec/86447/okunoin_2.webp 1024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/d913c8359beea7a1d1cf9e862f92a8ec/3bc27/okunoin_2.jpg 240w,\n/static/d913c8359beea7a1d1cf9e862f92a8ec/98431/okunoin_2.jpg 480w,\n/static/d913c8359beea7a1d1cf9e862f92a8ec/b3ee8/okunoin_2.jpg 960w,\n/static/d913c8359beea7a1d1cf9e862f92a8ec/1f853/okunoin_2.jpg 1024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/d913c8359beea7a1d1cf9e862f92a8ec/b3ee8/okunoin_2.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Okunoin\"\n          title=\"Okunoin\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>  </p>\n<p>I could hear monk’s preach at a place to rest in Okunoin.<br>\nHe told me about the following waka.  </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">高野山　結ぶ庵に袖朽ちて　苔の下にぞ　有明の月</code></pre></div>\n<p>I was moved by the beauty…<br>\nI felt sure that I came here to hear this waka.  </p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/00703973f4fbd8ad75c969c50fd2a25a/1f853/bentendake.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.59375%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/00703973f4fbd8ad75c969c50fd2a25a/01472/bentendake.webp 240w,\n/static/00703973f4fbd8ad75c969c50fd2a25a/222bd/bentendake.webp 480w,\n/static/00703973f4fbd8ad75c969c50fd2a25a/620b9/bentendake.webp 960w,\n/static/00703973f4fbd8ad75c969c50fd2a25a/86447/bentendake.webp 1024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/00703973f4fbd8ad75c969c50fd2a25a/3bc27/bentendake.jpg 240w,\n/static/00703973f4fbd8ad75c969c50fd2a25a/98431/bentendake.jpg 480w,\n/static/00703973f4fbd8ad75c969c50fd2a25a/b3ee8/bentendake.jpg 960w,\n/static/00703973f4fbd8ad75c969c50fd2a25a/1f853/bentendake.jpg 1024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/00703973f4fbd8ad75c969c50fd2a25a/b3ee8/bentendake.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Bentendake\"\n          title=\"Bentendake\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>  </p>\n<p>After visitting Okunoin, I climbed Bentendake from Daimon.<br>\nTrees healed my heart and body. It was a blessing.  </p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/a3fff45ef86216b6a749d1b27f12d820/1f853/sankonomatsu.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.59375%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/a3fff45ef86216b6a749d1b27f12d820/01472/sankonomatsu.webp 240w,\n/static/a3fff45ef86216b6a749d1b27f12d820/222bd/sankonomatsu.webp 480w,\n/static/a3fff45ef86216b6a749d1b27f12d820/620b9/sankonomatsu.webp 960w,\n/static/a3fff45ef86216b6a749d1b27f12d820/86447/sankonomatsu.webp 1024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/a3fff45ef86216b6a749d1b27f12d820/3bc27/sankonomatsu.jpg 240w,\n/static/a3fff45ef86216b6a749d1b27f12d820/98431/sankonomatsu.jpg 480w,\n/static/a3fff45ef86216b6a749d1b27f12d820/b3ee8/sankonomatsu.jpg 960w,\n/static/a3fff45ef86216b6a749d1b27f12d820/1f853/sankonomatsu.jpg 1024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/a3fff45ef86216b6a749d1b27f12d820/b3ee8/sankonomatsu.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Sanko no Matsu\"\n          title=\"Sanko no Matsu\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>  </p>\n<p>This time I could have great experiences.<br>\nI’d love to go again.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/forests-in-mt-koya/","tagSlugs":["/tag/buddhism/","/tag/mt-koya/","/tag/kukai/","/tag/dake-no-benzaiten/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2019-10-06T10:00:00Z","description":"The first time I went to Mt.Koya. The purpose of this time was greeting Kukai-san and Dake-no-benzaiten-san...","tags":["Buddhism","Mt.Koya","Kukai","Dake-no-benzaiten"],"title":"Forests in Mt.Koya","socialImage":"/media/okunoin.jpg"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/posts/forests-in-mt-koya/"}}}